ESP-Daemon firmware private libraries
====================================

This folder contains project modules compiled as static libraries by PlatformIO.

Design notes
------------
- `src/main.cpp` is intentionally thin and only wires startup flow.
- Feature logic lives in `lib/<module>/` folders.
- Runtime behavior is unchanged by this split; the goal is maintainability.

Module map
----------
- `app_settings/`
  - Settings schema, JSON serialization, validation, and NVS persistence.
  - `app_settings.cpp`: defaults, JSON load/store helpers, read access.
  - `app_settings_update.cpp`: update/validation flow.
  - `app_settings_storage.cpp`: save/reset/factory-reset and boot load.
- `web_server/`
  - HTTP server and web UI endpoints.
  - `web_server.cpp`: server bootstrap, static file serving, route registration.
  - `web_server_routes.cpp`: API handlers and settings import/export logic.
- `comm/`
  - ESP-NOW communication, emergency route runtime behavior.
- `wifi_config/`
  - Wi-Fi provisioning and identity refresh.
- `ros_node/`
  - micro-ROS publishers/subscribers and power control integration.
- `led_control/`
  - onboard NeoPixel behavior and LED task control.
- `sensors/`
  - ADC voltmeter sampling and sensor utility APIs.
- `battery_estimate/`
  - battery status estimation and export helpers.
- `telemetry_log/`
  - runtime telemetry buffer and JSON export for web API.

Guidelines
----------
- Keep cross-module dependencies directional (avoid circular includes).
- Prefer `.h/.cpp` modules over textual include patterns.
- Keep route registration in `web_server.cpp`; put handler implementation in
  `web_server_routes.cpp`.
